WORK SUMMARY:
Session continued with password hashing, which is a crucial security practice. The trainer explained that passwords should never be stored in plain text. Instead, 
they are converted into a hashed format using algorithms like bycrypt. Hashing ensures that even if the database is compromised, the original passwords cannot be easily 
retrieved. We also learned about salting, which adds an extra layer of security to hashed passwords


